# Frontend design (Listing & Claim Gate)

## Sources

- Follow shadcn/ui compose rules: use primitives first, `gap-*` not `space-y-*`,
  semantic tokens, no manual purple “AI slop” themes.
- App shell (not a marketing landing): Gate / Monitoring density over hero chrome.
- Illustrations only from `public/illustrations/` using docs/ILLUSTRATIONS.md prompts.

## Responsive

- Mobile-first. Gate: tabs stack; result below form on `<md`, split on `md+`.
- Monitoring: 2-col metrics on mobile, up to 6 on `lg`.
- Nav: collapse labels on small screens; keep touch targets ≥44px.

## Gate UX

- Two modes only for now: **Mock** (fetch products → analyze) and **Manual** (title+desc).
- Always show publish decision badge: PASS / REVIEW / REJECT.
- Pair ScoreCard with EfficiencyPanel when analysis returns efficiency_analysis.

## Do not

- Cards-for-decoration in empty states beyond one quiet panel.
- Inconsistent illustration styles or huge hero images.
- Platform-specific forms (Trendyol fields) until real adapters land.
